I can hardly say I was surprised at this; I asked-how much? He said he would count them, and thought about three shillings apiece (our money

I mean by this, of the value of our Government money; and not, literally, Government money; of which, indeed, I saw very little-very.
                  ) would be sufficient. As there were but fifteen, I did not think it high. I wondered if it had been the habit to charge this matter in the stationery account?
